@mattfarina @sdboyer - An example of a kit-type repo is [go-kit](https://github.com/go-kit/kit). 

You may opt to only use the [ratelimit](https://github.com/go-kit/kit/tree/master/ratelimit) and [circuitbalancer](https://github.com/go-kit/kit/tree/master/circuitbreaker) packages, and not the others. If you follow the practice of minimal vendoring (only vendor what you actually use), you may want to vendor this repo at the individual package level, not the project level.

Note: I'm not advocating that tools be capable of managing dependencies at the package level, only providing an example of what it might look like.
